In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump declares the third Saturday of each May as Armed Forces Day. He honors the brave men and women of the United States Armed Forces who have consistently defended the nation and its freedoms throughout history. The President expresses gratitude for their sacrifices and acknowledges the importance of ensuring that the military remains strong and well-equipped. He calls on Congress to increase funding for national defense and advocates for increased support for service members, including a 3.1 percent pay raise for 2020. The proclamation also encourages Americans to display the flag of the United States on Armed Forces Day and to learn more about military service.